narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: second half of ap calc bc
Integral calculus, series, taylor/maclaurin series/polynomials, polar and parametric calculus

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
teacher was not the best at explaining or engaging the class
our substitute teachers were much better
main point of improvement: standardise the teaching, maybe share the worksheets or slides among teachers?
all the content can be found on google / khan academy so if you can't go to class you can watch videos to catch up

Ultimately course was very effective at teaching the content, however it was not engaging. The explorations were dull and I often felt I learned very little from them. Classes were hit or miss and it was not until the problem sets that I solidified an understanding of the content.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: no, I think there are better or more useful QR credits available for non-STEM majors.
If a student is looking to/needs to learn integral calc then yes, otherwise no.
